4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would establish the Market
6 Accountability Compensation Fund in the State Treasury
7 for the purpose of providing monetary relief to victims
8 of investment fraud.
9 This bill would authorize the Alabama Securities
10 Commission to use the fund to provide restitution
11 assistance to victims of investment fraud who cannot
12 recover restitution from the perpetrator.
13 This bill would establish limits on the amount
14 that may be paid from the fund to victims of investment
15 fraud.
16 This bill would authorize the commission to have
17 subrogation rights to the restitution ordered for a
18 victim that has received a restitution assistance
19 award.
20 This bill would provide criminal penalties for
21 anyone who files a fraudulent claim or provides
22 misleading information to the commission regarding a
23 claim for restitution assistance.
24 This bill would also authorize the commission to
25 enforce this act.
